By Aderonke Ojediran Ugochukwu Nwagbo, one of the winners of BetKing AFKON campaign, at the just concluded 2021 Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) hosted by Cameroon has urged husbands to carry their wives along while betting. Nwagbo said this at BetKing award ceremony to celebrate the finale of its AFKON campaign and handover of brand new cars to winners of the campaign on Sunday in Lagos. He said that said carrying his wife along made it easy for him to bet. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that two brand new Sport Utility Vehicles (SUVs) valued at seven million Naira each were given out to winners of the “AFKON Campaign Finale”. Nwagbo told NAN that playing on the BetKing platform had made betting easy. “I bet without having to sneak around, my wife knows this, I carry her along, so it’s easy for me to bet without guilt, it’s a common knowledge in our home, no secret. “I have won several times but this is my biggest win so far, thank you BetKing for giving me a beautiful Valentine gift, I can’t wait to ride with my wife. “Playing on BetKing is so easy, they are truly the king makers, they have a very good odds, and cashing out is easy, no drama,” Nwagbo said. Sharing the same excitement was Joseph Onyemaechi, who told NAN that he had been patronising BetKing for three years, his stake goes as much as N100,000. “I am so happy I won, I came all the way from Anambra, BetKing is everywhere and I am happy to be king with them, winning this car is huge. “I stake as much as N100,000, the least I do is N50,000 and it’s such a dream come through for me to win a car,” Onyemaechi said. NAN reports that Nwagbo got a red SUV while Onyemechi got the brown coloured SUV. Austin Jay Jay Okocha, the Brand Ambassador of BetKing, urged the recipients to share the good news. “There are no magic here, I wish I could play too, perhaps I would have won this SUV I have been saving since I retired,” Okocha said. He applauded BetKing for bringing smiles to the faces of the winners. Oladapo Olasope, the Chief Financial Officer, BetKing, told NAN that the company was committed toward ensuring that they remain transparent. “Whatelse can I say, keep winning, our track record has consistently shown that we are committed toward giving a stress free betting experience,” he said. Olasope said that the company would have a similar event in commemoration of its four years anniversary. “At a soon to be announced date, we will celebrate our fourth year anniversary with our loyal clients, he said. (NAN) (www.nanews.ng)